  <h1>About Nike</h1>
  <p>Nike, Inc. is a renowned multinational corporation known for its athletic footwear, apparel, equipment, and accessories. It is one of the world's largest and most recognizable sports brands.</p>

  <h2>Key Highlights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Nike was founded on January 25, 1964, as Blue Ribbon Sports by Bill Bowerman and Phil Knight.</li>
    <li>The company's name was officially changed to Nike, Inc. on May 30, 1971.</li>
    <li>Nike's iconic swoosh logo was designed by graphic designer Carolyn Davidson in 1971 and represents the wing of the Greek goddess Nike, the goddess of victory.</li>
    <li>Nike is known for its commitment to innovation in sports technology, producing cutting-edge footwear and apparel for athletes and fitness enthusiasts.</li>
    <li>Some of Nike's most popular products include the Air Max, Air Jordan, and the Nike Dunk lines of athletic shoes.</li>
    <li>The brand sponsors numerous high-profile athletes and sports teams, including basketball star Michael Jordan and soccer clubs like FC Barcelona.</li>
    <li>Nike has a strong corporate responsibility program, emphasizing sustainability and social impact through initiatives like the "Move to Zero" campaign and community engagement programs.</li>
  </ul>

